The University Hotel (also known as University House) was a threestory hotels hotel that stood in the spot now occupied by Black Bear Diner. Opened by Dr. Edwin Liebfried in September 1915, it was was a nice establishment for its time. It featured steam heating, hot and cold running water, and meals served in the dining room.

The building became a fraternity frat house in the 1960s and was eventually demolished in 1971. Soon after, Sambos was built on the lot.
